Fan-Out Questions
ï¿¼
Fan-Out questions are information-seeking questions that require some information about a list of entities
They are commonly found in day-to-day scenarios:
Performing a literature review (fan-out over papers)
Planning a trip (fan-out over attractions, hotels, etc)
Choosing where to eat (fan-out over restaurants)
Easy (but tedious) for humans to solve, but challenging for LLMs due to the amount of information needed
